## OSINT Platform — Elasticsearch JVM tuning
##
## Heap size (-Xms/-Xmx) is set dynamically at launch time by launcher.py
## via the ES_JAVA_OPTS env var; do NOT set it here.

## Garbage collector — G1 is the ES 8.x default and is right for desktop.
-XX:+UseG1GC

## Pre-touch heap pages on start so first queries don't pay page-fault tax.
-XX:+AlwaysPreTouch

## Disable explicit GC calls from libraries.
-XX:+DisableExplicitGC

## Reasonable defaults for a single-user desktop instance.
-Xss1m
-Djava.awt.headless=true
-Dfile.encoding=UTF-8
-Djna.nosys=true

## Errors / heap dumps land in the user's logs dir (path injected at runtime).
-XX:+HeapDumpOnOutOfMemoryError
-XX:+ExitOnOutOfMemoryError

## Network stack — IPv4 first, ES has historical IPv6 quirks.
-Djava.net.preferIPv4Stack=true

## Required JDK module opens for ES 8.x on bundled JDK 21.
17-:-Djava.security.manager=allow
